; 1. generic operations with explicit dispatch
; -- new operations: no changes to the existing ops 
; -- new types: has to change all the existing ops
; 2. data-directed style
; -- new ops: has to change all data types
; -- new types: no changes to the existing ops
; 3. message-passing style
; -- new ops: has to change all data types
; -- new types: no changes to the existing ops
;
; The data-directed or message-passing would be
; most appropriate for a system in which new types must often
; be added.
;
; The generic operations with explicit dispatch would be most
; appropriate for a system in which new operations must often
; be added.
